grin-get is the program used to perform installations of grin-get compatible packages. Package names are formatted as User/Repo[/Version], where the version is optional.

For help with the grin api, use help grin-api

Usage:
    grin-get <install | remove> ...

grin-get install <package>
    Instructs grin-get to install the specified package.

grin-get remove <package>
    Instructs grin-get to remove the specified package from the system.